  "prompt": "What is the greatest Christmas song of all time?",
  "response": "The \"greatest\" Christmas song is subjective and varies based on personal preferences, cultural influences, and traditions. However, some Christmas songs have achieved widespread acclaim and timeless popularity. Here are a few contenders often cited as the greatest:\n\n1. **\"All I Want for Christmas Is You\" by Mariah Carey (1994)**  \n   A modern classic that has become a holiday staple, breaking records and topping charts worldwide.\n\n2. **\"White Christmas\" by Bing Crosby (1942)**  \n   One of the best-selling singles of all time, this nostalgic song by Bing Crosby is synonymous with the holiday season.\n\n3. **\"Last Christmas\" by Wham! (1984)**  \n   A bittersweet yet catchy tune that has remained a holiday favorite for decades.\n\n4. **\"The Christmas Song (Chestnuts Roasting on an Open Fire)\" by Nat King Cole (1946)**  \n   A cozy and timeless song that captures the warmth of the season.\n\n5. **\"Jingle Bell Rock\" by Bobby Helms (1957)**  \n   A festive, upbeat track that\u2019s a go-to for holiday parties and celebrations.\n\n6. **\"Silent Night\" (Traditional, 1818)**  \n   A beloved carol with deep spiritual meaning and universal appeal.\n\n7. **\"Fairytale of New York\" by The Pogues featuring Kirsty MacColl (1987)**  \n   A rugged yet heartfelt ballad embraced by fans for its raw storytelling.\n\nUltimately, the \"greatest\" Christmas song depends on what resonates most with you\u2014whether it\u2019s nostalgia, melody, or lyrics. What\u2019s your favorite?",
